03/11/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- An earthquake measuring 5.4 on the Richter scale struck central Serbia early Wednesday (November 3rd) killing a couple whose roof collapsed on them. 
About 50 other people were injured by the quake. 
The epicentre was 10km north of Kraljevo. 
Several buildings, especially older ones, sustained damage. 
The earthquake, felt across Serbia as well as in neighbouring Bulgaria, was followed by four minor aftershocks.
Meanwhile, a quake measuring 5.1 on the Richter scale struck Turkey and Greece early Wednesday. 
Its epicentre was around 35km northwest of Canakkale. 
No casualties or damage has been reported. 
Seismologists say the quakes are unrelated. 
(Tanjug, RTS, Beta, B92, Anadolu news agency, Hurriyet, Novinite - 03/11/10)
